On Sun, 25 Jan 2004, Harry Hoffman wrote:

> I'm having some issues with my sliding door and hope you can help. It
> seems like the top roller has cut a groove in the channel.
>
> Is the roller supposed to roll? Or should the channel simply be
> heavily greased? Or both?

The roller should definitely roll.  There should be some lubrication in
the track, but unless you want it dripping on you head next summer it
should not be "heavily" greased.

